[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    11[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThis is the tenth and final recipe in Chapter 5 and the chapter's fourth Complex-tier recipe (four-star complexity). It introduces the recipe-specific concepts that distinguish it from the prior entity-resolution recipes (5.1 patient, 5.2 provider, 5.3 address, 5.4 eligibility, 5.5 cross-facility, 5.6 claims-clinical, 5.7 longitudinal-name-change, 5.8 privacy-preserving, 5.9 national-scale TEFCA): the matching core is the same probabilistic-record-linkage core used elsewhere but the operational scaffolding is what makes the recipe complex; the data-source heterogeneity is high (SSA Limited Access Death Master File, state vital-records offices, payer death feeds, EHR-recorded deaths, hospice deaths, family-reported deaths, obituary feeds, claims-cessation inferences, provider-reported deaths); the timing dynamics are non-trivial (death events lag by days to months across the source landscape); the downstream-impact landscape is broad (every operational system that consumes the MPI changes behavior on death status, with named per-system cascade-propagation cadences); the failure modes are dignity-affecting in ways that other recipes are not (the family on the receiving end of the institution's wrong-patient correspondence is a real person experiencing real grief); the legal-and-compliance overlay (HIPAA's 50-year posthumous-protection period, the personal-representative framework, the jurisdictional vital-records rules) is its own program of work; the premature-death-report rate is small but operationally non-trivial with patient-disruption-and-institutional-reputation cost; the hidden-duplicate-revelation pattern is recipe-specific and creates coordinated-resolution complexity with recipe 5.1; the multi-decade post-death record lifecycle exceeds most institutional planning cycles; and the family-experience-as-load-bearing observation reframes the work from data-integration to institutional-dignity-program. The opening Tuesday-morning vignette earns its position: the chemotherapy-infusion-appointment-reminder voice call to a daughter whose mother died on a Saturday in February, the listening-to-the-entire-message-before-she-hangs-up framing, the brother's call from cardiology last week, the aunt's patient-satisfaction-survey two days after the obituary, the billing-cycle-statement coming next week with the marketing insert about the cardiology screening program because the patient was over sixty-five and the marketing segmentation rule selected her for the campaign, sets up the cascade of operational vignettes (large IDN MPI with no automated SSA or state vital-records feed, Medicare Advantage payer with the CMS Medicare Beneficiary Database and the premature-death-report reversal experience, state immunization registry with monthly-but-variable vital-records submission and probabilistic matching with both false-negative and false-positive deaths, clinical research data warehouse with four-source date-of-death reconciliation, accountable-care-organization analytics with HEDIS and CMS Star Ratings deceased-patient handling, legal-and-compliance with the 50-year posthumous-protection period and personal-representative framework, hospice agency with the most-accurate-but-locked-inside-the-operational-silo death information, TEFCA Qualified Health Information Network with cross-network-discrepancy reconciliation, national pharmacy chain with deceased-patient-pharmacy-fraud-detection, federal Social Security Administration's Death Master File access framework, family member of a deceased patient receiving wrong-record correspondence) at exactly the right level of "this is what deceased-patient resolution actually looks like in production" energy.[K
