[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    19[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThat said, two correctness-and-compliance gaps at HIGH severity need attention before publication, plus a recipe-specific set of MEDIUM and LOW items. (1) The architecture invokes a per-source ingestion Lambda authenticating inbound source feeds (with per-source authentication varying by source: LADMF subscription credentials, state-vital-records-feed credentials, payer-feed credentials including CMS MBD's mTLS, hospice-agency credentials, family-reported-death intake authentication through the patient-services call center, obituary-feed credentials, provider-reported-death intake), a death-event-matcher Lambda, a multi-source-reconciler Lambda, a premature-death-report-verification-router Lambda, a hidden-duplicate-revealer Lambda coordinating with recipe 5.1 atomically, an mpi-update-handler Lambda, per-system-cascade Lambdas (appointment-canceller, active-prescription-reviewer, billing-episode-closer, communication-path-switcher, portal-access-handler), a premature-death-report-reversal Lambda with dual-control approval and verifier-authorization validation, the EventBridge fan-out reaching recipes 5.1 / 5.5 / 5.7 / 5.8 / 5.9 plus per-system operational consumers plus 3.6 / 7.x / 12.x, the personal-representative-portal Cognito-mediated authorization flow with institutional release-of-information system integration, and the per-source-credential rotation lifecycle; the identity-boundary checks on these paths are not specified at the architectural level. The recipe's own TODO at the IAM Permissions row names the chapter-wide pattern from 5.1 / 5.4 / 5.5 / 5.6 / 5.7 / 5.8 / 5.9 with explicit recipe-specific extensions (the per-source-credential rotation's per-jurisdiction stakes, the family-reported-death-intake authentication-and-verification stakes, the personal-representative-portal authorization-mediation stakes, the dual-controlled high-impact-update routing through manual approval) but the architecture text does not actually specify the producer-signed envelope, the per-Lambda execution-role binding, the dual-control mechanism for the reversal pathway, the family-reported-death-intake worker-authentication-and-verification framework, or the cross-recipe event acceptance criteria. The consequence is uniquely sharp here because the deceased-patient-resolution pipeline operates against patient-affecting downstream systems with cascade consequences (a forged death event applied without verification produces patient-impersonation-grade insurance termination and prescription cancellation and portal-access suspension; a forged premature-death-report reversal could re-activate an actually-deceased patient's records and trigger unauthorized post-death disclosure under the wrong personal-representative-framework; a forged family-reported-death intake could be used to silently terminate a target patient's care; a forged personal-representative authorization could grant unauthorized post-death PHI disclosure during the estate-administration period; a forged cross-recipe event into 5.1 / 5.5 / 5.7 / 5.8 / 5.9 / 3.6 / 7.x / 12.x could cascade through the entity-resolution chapter and into the broader analytics infrastructure). (2) The cohort-stratified accuracy monitoring is structurally absent from the architecture pattern. The recipe correctly elevates four operational metrics in the Honest Take and the Where-It-Struggles section (mean-time-to-recognize-death, false-positive-death-rate, family-correspondence-after-death rate, cross-system-propagation-completeness) and adds the premature-death-report-reversal latency and the personal-representative-record-request completion time as additional operational metrics, but the architecture does not specify cohort-stratified versions of any of these metrics. The cohort-stratified-disparity stakes are recipe-specific and uniquely consequential because: (a) the premature-death-report rate may be systematically higher for cohorts with common names, ambiguous demographic data, or naming conventions less well-represented in the source-data-quality calibration (the SSA DMF's premature-death-report-rate baseline is computed at the population level; per-cohort variation may be substantial but is invisible without stratification); (b) the family-correspondence-after-death rate disparity is the most family-visible signal of the institution's deceased-patient-resolution discipline and is a fairness signal at the population scale (institutions with worse coverage for rural patients, non-English-speaking families, communities with less robust vital-records integration produce systematic differential family-experience disparities); (c) the mean-time-to-recognize-death disparity tracks population coverage of authoritative sources (deaths outside healthcare facilities, deaths in jurisdictions with slower-to-modernize vital-records feeds, deaths in populations less covered by SSA's institutional reporting infrastructure produce systematic recognition-latency disparities); (d) the false-negative-death rate by cohort interacts with quality-measurement-pipeline bias (cohorts with lower death-recognition rates remain in measure denominators they should be excluded from, biasing the quality scores across the cohort dimension); (e) the personal-representative-record-request completion time disparity reflects institutional support for families whose primary language is not English, families navigating estate administration without legal representation, or families in states with diverging posthumous-protection rules. Same chapter pattern as 5.1 / 5.4 / 5.5 / 5.6 / 5.7 / 5.8 / 5.9 Finding A1; the cohort-distribution stakes are recipe-specific because deceased-patient-resolution disparities are simultaneously fairness signals AND family-dignity signals AND quality-measurement-bias signals, and the privacy team plus the equity-monitoring committee plus the patient-experience and patient-advocacy functions plus the institutional governance committee for cross-jurisdictional posthumous-protection overlays are all explicit reviewers.[K
