[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This is the fourth recipe in Chapter 11 (Conversational AI / Virtual Assistants) and the chapter's first recipe to combine adaptive conversational interviewing with structured clinical-data capture, validated screener administration, and parallel crisis-and-acuity flagging as architectural primitives. It establishes the chapter's adaptive-interview discipline (per-visit-type protocol-as-code lifecycle, validated-screener-library governance, acuity-pattern-library governance, pre-visit-packet-as-clinical-team-facing contract, crisis-and-acuity-flagging as parallel pipeline, structured-extraction with schema validation, resumability as architectural primitive, EHR-side-display configuration as deployment prerequisite, per-cohort equity monitoring with launch-gate discipline) and frames the chapter's posture toward intake bots as institutional clinical-workflow products that happen to use conversational AI rather than as conversational AI products that happen to collect intake data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The opening Marisol-with-the-fourteen-page-PDF vignette earns its position. The text-message Monday morning, the lunch-break completion attempt, the eighty-six-checkbox review of systems, the 14% phone battery, the two-line chief complaint, the family-history detail (paternal grandfather at forty-eight) that gets lost because the form doesn't ask the right follow-up, the fifteen-minute appointment that runs over because the form's data was thin enough that Dr. Adekunle re-asks everything, the constellation of features (chest tightness plus exertional pattern plus family history of early heart disease) that an experienced clinical assistant would chase with adaptive follow-ups but the form does not. The "what makes a great intake is not what makes a great form" framing is the recipe's clearest articulation of the form-versus-conversation primitive that grounds the rest of the recipe. The "the bot does not tell Marisol that she might be having cardiac symptoms (it is a chatbot, not a clinician). It quietly flags the encounter for a same-day call from a triage nurse" framing is the recipe's strongest single passage on the bot-as-data-collector-not-clinician primitive in clinical-action context.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Technology section is the chapter's introductory pedagogy on adaptive-conversational-interviewing-plus-structured-clinical-data-capture for healthcare and executes at the right grain. The "Why Pre-Visit Intake Has Stayed Stuck on Forms" subsection grounds the form-engine-with-static-branching failure mode in a specific architectural diagnosis. The "What an Adaptive Intake Bot Actually Does" subsection's nine-stage decomposition (greeting and disclosure, chief complaint and reason for visit, history of present illness, relevant review of systems, medication confirmation, allergy confirmation, relevant past medical/surgical/family/social history, visit-type-specific screeners and protocols, advance-directive/code-status/patient-rights items, crisis-detection and acuity-flag layer, closing summary, structured pre-visit packet generation) is correctly granular. The "Why a Generic LLM Cannot Run a Pre-Visit Intake" subsection's seven-property enumeration is recipe-distinct and earns its position as the recipe's clearest articulation of the why-naked-LLM-in-front-of-intake-conversation-is-not-an-intake-bot primitive. The "What the Intake Bot Has To Do That the Refill Bot Did Not" subsection's five-property enumeration (adaptive question-flow orchestration, validated-screener administration as a discrete tool, structured clinical-data extraction with schema validation, crisis and acuity flagging as a parallel pipeline, pre-visit packet generation as a structured handoff to the clinical workflow) is the recipe's clearest articulation of the intake-bot-vs-refill-bot-distinction primitive. The "Intake Reality" subsection's twelve-property enumeration earns its position as the recipe's strongest single passage on the intake-conversation-is-different-from-other-conversational-cases primitive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The ten-stage architecture (channel entry, input safety screening, identity and relationship verification, visit-context loading, protocol selection, adaptive question-flow orchestration, structured extraction and screeners, parallel crisis and acuity flagging, output safety screening, pre-visit packet generation) is the right shape and recipe-distinct from 11.3's nine-stage decomposition. The two new architectural primitives (visit-context loading with chart-and-prior-intake awareness, protocol selection as first orchestration decision) and the recipe-distinct cross-cutting design points (intake-protocol-as-code lifecycle organized per visit type, validated-screener-library governance separately, pre-visit-packet schema as clinical-team-facing contract, crisis-and-acuity-flagging as architectural floor running in parallel, medication-and-allergy-reconciliation-do-not-modify-chart, conversation-log-as-rich-PHI-and-clinical-record, per-cohort monitoring with intake-specific metric slices, resumability-as-architectural-primitive, EHR-side-packet-display-as-part-of-deployment) are correctly elevated.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Why-These-Services section walks each AWS component back to the conceptual primitive it implements. The Honest Take is strong, with eight traps earning the recipe's voice (institutional-content-as-someone-else's-problem recast as per-visit-type-protocol-library-and-validated-screener-library-and-acuity-pattern-library-and-pre-visit-packet-schema-as-someone-else's-problem with three-to-six-months-of-formalization-as-pre-deployment-investment; underestimating-the-validated-screener-layer with the paraphrasing-invalidates-the-score framing; underestimating-the-crisis-and-acuity-layer with the highest-density-disclosure-surface-in-the-patient-experience framing; shipping-with-too-narrow-a-scope; shipping-with-too-broad-a-scope with the bot-not-triage-bot-not-diagnostic-bot-not-decision-support-tool framing; treating-EHR-side-display-as-someone-else's-problem with the beautiful-packet-that-no-clinician-reads-is-worthless framing; shipping-without-per-cohort-equity-monitoring; shipping-without-resumability). The "thing that surprises engineers" / "thing that surprises clinical leaders" cross-discipline-comparisons earn their positions. The closing "the intake bot is the right fourth recipe in this chapter, after the FAQ bot, the scheduling bot, and the refill bot, because it builds on the patterns those bots established and adds the patterns that the rest of the chapter will need" frames the intake-bot-as-fourth-recipe-that-builds-the-adaptive-interview-substrate thesis.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m That said, three correctness-and-compliance gaps at HIGH severity need attention before publication, plus the chapter-pattern set of MEDIUM and LOW items.
