[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (1) **Intake-protocol-as-code lifecycle and validated-screener-library and acuity-pattern-library governance scaffolding underspecified despite explicit prose elevation.** The recipe correctly elevates intake-protocol-as-versioned-governance-artifact-organized-per-visit-type, validated-screener-library-governed-separately, and acuity-pattern-library-with-named-clinical-ownership in three separate places. Despite this prose elevation, the architecture pattern, the diagram, and the pseudocode treat the protocol-and-screener-and-pattern governance as institutional-policy reference rather than as architectural primitives with version-control discipline, sandbox-testing-and-staged-rollout-policy per-visit-type, screener-library re-validation-cadence on wording changes, acuity-pattern-library quarterly-review-with-named-patient-safety-committee-ownership, per-protocol-version stamping and per-screener-bundle-version stamping and per-acuity-pattern-version stamping on every pre-visit-packet record. Recipe-acute amplification because the intake bot's quality is bounded above by all three artifacts simultaneously and the chapter's first parallel-pipeline primitive (crisis-and-acuity flagging) depends on the pattern library's named ownership.
