[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (2) **Pre-visit-packet journal and tool-call ledger accumulate per-conversation content with potentially-PHI-rich free-text outside archive-reference pattern, with recipe-distinct medical-records-retention-floor and conversation-log-as-clinical-record amplifications.** Same chapter pattern as 11.3 with recipe-distinct extensions. The Step 8C pre_visit_packet_journal write includes the structured packet's full HPI free-text, full ROS findings, full medication-reconciliation deltas, full allergy-reconciliation deltas, full screener responses (item-level), full new-information events. The Step 5C audit_tool_call writes for protocol_selector, hpi_extraction, ros_extraction, medication_reconciliation_capture, allergy_reconciliation_capture, history_extraction, screener_administer include the full extraction outputs and patient-stated-context. The recipe-distinct dimensions include the pre-visit-packet journal's medical-records retention floor (longer than HIPAA's six-year minimum in many states; some states extend retention "until the patient turns 18 plus N years" for pediatric records, recipe-acute given the recipe's pediatric-and-proxy-completion variation), the per-record-class access-control surface (the packet journal is part of the institution's clinical-administrative record with restricted access surface including prescribers, the conversation log is part of the clinical-record-by-some-institutions and part of the audit-pipeline-by-others, the tool-call ledger is part of the audit pipeline; each record class has different retention, access-control, and disclosure-accounting profiles), and the cross-correlation discipline with the institution's encounter records and FHIR QuestionnaireResponse records.
