[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (3) **Per-cohort completion-rate-and-screener-positivity-and-acuity-flag-rate monitoring with launch-gate discipline architecturally implicit despite recipe's own elevation as central trap, with recipe-distinct multi-axis cohort and mis-extraction-rate-as-clinical-record-quality-acute-metric extensions.** Same chapter pattern as 11.3 Finding A1, with recipe-distinct extensions. The recipe correctly elevates per-cohort monitoring in four separate places (Cross-Cutting Design Points, Production-Gaps, Honest Take's seventh trap, Where-it-Struggles cross-language accuracy gaps). Despite this thorough prose elevation, the architecture pattern, the diagram, and the pseudocode (Step 10D cloudwatch.put_metric calls) do not specify per-cohort launch-gate threshold values, two-axis and three-axis cohort stratification (per-language-by-visit-type, per-language-by-channel, per-visit-type-by-age-cohort, per-channel-by-proxy-completion, per-language-by-channel-by-visit-type for multilingual-multi-visit-type deployments), per-cohort mis-extraction-rate as recipe-distinct clinical-record-quality-acute metric (HPI-or-ROS-or-medication-or-allergy-or-history misextraction has clinical-record-quality consequences a wrong scheduling action does not), per-cohort screener-administration-fidelity rate (validated-wording preservation as recipe-distinct), per-cohort packet-delivery-success rate, per-cohort EHR-side-clinician-acknowledgment rate (recipe-distinct: did the clinician actually read the packet during the visit), per-cohort crisis-flag-rate-and-acuity-flag-rate as equity-and-clinical-safety-acute. Recipe-acute amplification because the intake bot is the chapter's first adaptive-interview-bot and the patient-experience improvements the recipe sells are bounded above by the per-cohort equity profile and the per-cohort clinical-record-quality profile.
