[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   1. **The pre-visit-packet journal is the recipe's load-bearing clinical-record artifact.** Object Lock in compliance mode for the medical-records-retention window aligns with the audit pipeline retention; the pre-visit-packet journal also has medical-records retention obligations that may be longer than the audit-pipeline retention floor (per-state medical-records retention rules vary; some are 7 years, some 10 years, some "until the patient turns 18 plus N years," some indefinite for certain record classes). For pediatric patients the retention floor is materially longer in many states; the recipe's pediatric-and-proxy-completion variation makes this recipe-acute. The architecture should specify the per-state medical-records retention floor reconciliation, the per-pediatric-record retention extension, and the per-record-class retention regime distinct from the audit-archive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   2. **The packet's HPI free-text, ROS findings, medication-reconciliation deltas, allergy-reconciliation deltas, history updates, and screener responses are clinical-record elements.** Each has its own retention and access-control profile (some history elements are not part of the formal medical record at all; some screener responses have specific access-control rules; some medication-reconciliation deltas are clinical-decision-support events with their own audit profile).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   3. **The screener responses include item-level data with crisis-sensitivity tags.** PHQ-9 item 9 (suicidal ideation), AUDIT-C items (problem alcohol use), domestic-violence-screener items, and substance-use items all have heightened sensitivity. The packet record's screener_records embed item-level responses. The architecture should specify the per-screener-item access-control surface (some institutions restrict access to item-9 responses to behavioral-health staff; some restrict the item-level data while exposing only the score band).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   4. **The patient's natural-language utterances throughout intake are potentially crisis-sensitive.** A patient mentioning intimate-partner violence, child abuse, elder abuse, or substance-use crisis embeds the disclosure in the conversation log and possibly in the structured history finding. The architecture should specify the per-disclosure-class handling (sensitive disclosures route to a separately-governed sensitive-disclosure surface with restricted access).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   5. **The conversation log is rich PHI and a clinical record.** The recipe's prose correctly elevates this. The architecture should specify the per-record-class retention reconciliation (audit-archive retention vs pre-visit-packet-journal retention vs conversation-log retention vs flag-event-journal retention may differ; some institutions treat the conversation log as part of the formal medical record while others treat it as an audit-pipeline artifact).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   6. **The per-record-class access-control surface is not specified.** The audit pipeline's access-control surface is the audit-and-compliance team plus the privacy officer. The pre-visit-packet-journal's access-control surface is the medical-records team plus the operations team plus the audit-and-compliance team plus the patient-rights handlers plus prescribers (read access for retrospective review) plus the patient (through the patient-portal access). The flag-events table's access-control surface is the patient-safety committee plus the clinical-staff-routing operators. The tool-call-ledger's access-control surface is the engineering team plus the audit-and-compliance team for incident review. Each record class has different access-control needs.
